The Marcosians were a Valentinian sect noted for their pronounced use of magical incantations, and arithmetical mysticism, deduced from the numerical value of the letters of the alphabet, by which they designated the Valentinian Aeone. The puerilities oi Marcue' system, and his gross charlatanism with a view to gsining an immoral ascendency over women, are fully described by Irenaeus i. 7 ff„ who is followedby Hippoi vi. 39; Epiph. Hoer. 34. Marcus seems to have lived in Asia Minor as a contemporary of Irenaeus‚ but his teaching was rife also in the neighbourhood oi Lyon (Iren. Le).
